    <etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
            ><lang/><w>*para-mrā-</w></mentioned> через ступени %i*fæl-mra%i → %ifæl-ra-%i →
        %ifælla-%i. Глагол %imra-%i ← %imla-%i ← %imle-%i ← %imel-%i — общеиндоевропейский. Исходное
        значение — ‘размягчать(ся) путем мятия, дубления, растирания’. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>mrā-</w><gloss><q>размягчать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>дубить</q></gloss></mentioned>, (в <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>mrātəm čarəma</w><gloss><q>дубленая кожа</q></gloss></mentioned>),
            <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>mla-</w><gloss><q>становиться вялым,
                дряблым</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><w/><gloss><q>слабеть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>млеть</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ga"
                ><lang/><w>mláith</w><gloss><q>мягкий</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ga"><w/><gloss><q>нежный</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                ><lang/><w>βλάξ</w><gloss><q>слабый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>вялый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>ленивый</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><lang/><w>flaccus</w><gloss><q>дряблый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>вислый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>вислоухий</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Исходя из метатезы %i*mle-%i
        || %i*mel-%i, относят сюда же индоевропейские слова со значением ‘молоть’, ‘мельница’
            (<mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>млѣти</w><gloss><q>молоть</q></gloss></mentioned> и
        пр.). Вс. %sМиллер%s (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
            /><biblScope>64</biblScope></bibl>) делит %ifæ-llajyn%i на %ifæ-mlā-y-un%i, забывая, что
        для осетинского надо исходить из формы %imrā-%i, а не %imlā-%i (ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>mrā-</w></mentioned>); а в этом случае появление %iI%i остается
        необъяснимым. Если же исходить из %ifæl-mrā-%i, то %ill%i окажется естественным результатом
        упрощения и ассимиляции группы %i-lmr-%i.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It probably traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                ><lang/><w>*para-mrā-</w></mentioned> through the stages %i*fæl-mra%i → %ifæl-ra-%i
        → %ifælla-%i. The verb %imra-%i ← %imla-%i ← %imle-%i ← %imel-%i is a general Indo-European
        verb. The initial meaning is ‘soften by crushing, tanning, rubbing’. Cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>mrā-</w><gloss><q>soften</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>tan</q></gloss></mentioned>, (in <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>mrātəm čarəma</w><gloss><q>tanned leather</q></gloss></mentioned>),
            <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>mla-</w><gloss><q>become faded,
            flabby</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
            ><w/><gloss><q>weaken</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>faint</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ga"
                ><lang/><w>mláith</w><gloss><q>soft</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ga"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>tender</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                ><lang/><w>βλάξ</w><gloss><q>weak</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>flabby</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>lazy</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><lang/><w>flaccus</w><gloss><q>flaccid</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>lop-eared</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Basing on the
        metathesis %i*mle-%i || %i*mel-%i, some people relate to it Indo-European words with the
        meaning ‘grind’, ‘mill’ (<mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                ><lang/><w>млѣти</w><gloss><q>grind</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр.). Ws. %sMiller%s
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>64</biblScope></bibl>) divides
        %ifæ-llajyn%i into %ifæ-mlā-y-un%i, forgetting that for Ossetic one should base on the form
        %imrā-%i, not on the %imlā-%i (cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>mrā-</w></mentioned>);
        and in this case the appearance of %iI%i remains unexplained. On the contrary, if one bases
        on %ifæl-mrā-%i, then %ill%i will turn out to be a natural result of the simplification and
        assimilation of the group %i-lmr-%i.</etym>
